      • testGetIndexInfoUnique

        public void testGetIndexInfoUnique()
                            throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests unique indexes. Primary key indexes are unique but foreign key indexes are not. Originally these two were the only index types supported by the ofbiz index creation code. The unique flag was used to distinguish between them. Since adding support for arbitrary indexes which may or may not be unique, we test to check that both are detected.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
